BusinessName.BusinessNameLine1Txt: JERSEY CITY UAW SENIOR CITIZENS HOUSING

IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: JERSEY CITY UAW'S MISSION IS TO SERVE A PUBLIC PURPOSE AND PROVIDE AND PROMOTE AFFORDABLE HOUSING OPPORTUNITIES TO LOW AND MODERATE INCOME DISABLED OR SENIOR CITIZENS IN NEW JERSEY. SPECIFICALLY, JERSEY CITY UAW WILL CONTINUE TO OPERATE THE HOUSING COMMUNITY PURSUANT TO A STATE ALLOWING FOR THE INCORPORATION OF NON-PROFIT ENTITIES TO DEVELOP AND OPERATE AFFORDABLE HOUSING.
IRS990.MissionDesc: JERSEY CITY UAW'S MISSION IS TO SERVE A PUBLIC PURPOSE AND PROVIDE AND PROMOTE AFFORDABLE HOUSING OPPORTUNITIES TO LOW AND MODERATE INCOME DISABLED OR SENIOR CITIZENS IN NEW JERSEY. SPECIFICALLY, JERSEY CITY UAW WILL CONTINUE TO OPERATE THE HOUSING COMMUNITY PURSUANT TO A STATE ALLOWING FOR THE INCORPORATION OF NON-PROFIT ENTITIES TO DEVELOP AND OPERATE AFFORDABLE HOUSING.
IRS990.Desc: JERSEY CITY UAW PROVIDES AFFORDABLE AND SUBSIDIZED HOUSING TO INDIVIDUALS BASED ON THEIR NEED AND THEIR MEETING CERTAIN SPECIFIED STANDARDS REQUIRED BY EITHER THE US DEPARTMENT OF HOUSING AND URBAN DEVELOPMENT OR THE NJ HOUSING AND MORTGAGE FINANCE AGENCY. JERSEY CITY UAW LIMITS THE RENTAL OF THE APARTMENTS TO THOSE INDIVIDUALS WHO QUALIFY FOR THE AFFORDABLE HOUSING PROGRAMS THAT THE COMMUNITY IS PART OF THROUGH DEED RESTRICTIONS AND FINANCIAL AGREEMENTS WITH HUD OR HMFA AND THEREFORE SHALL REQUIRE INCOME QUALIFICATIONS FOR THOSE PROGRAMS AS REQUIRED BY FEDERAL AND STATE LAW. GENERALLY, SINCE AFFORDABLE HOUSING IS LIMITED TO LOW-INCOME FAMILIES AND INDIVIDUALS, ELIGIBILITY IS BASED UPON THE FOLLOWING CRITERIA: (1) ANNUAL GROSS INCOME; (2) WHETHER A PERSON QUALIFIES AS ELDERLY, A PERSON WITH A DISABILITY, OR AS A FAMILY; AND (3) U.S. CITIZENSHIP OR ELIGIBLE IMMIGRATION STATUS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CORPORATION IS A NOT-FOR-PROFIT ORGANIZATION THAT IS EXEMPT FROM INCOME TAXES UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE AND CLASSIFIED BY THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE AS OTHER THAN A PRIVATE FOUNDATION. THE CORPORATION IS ALSO EXEMPT UNDER TITLE 15 OF THE STATE OF NEW JERSEY CORPORATIONS AND ASSOCIATIONS NOT-FOR-PROFIT ACT. ACCORDINGLY, NO PROVISION FOR FEDERAL OR STATE INCOME TAX HAS BEEN PRESENTED IN THE ACCOMPANYING FINANCIAL STATEMENTS. AS REQUIRED BY LAW, THE CORPORATION FILES AN INFORMATIONAL RETURN WITH THE FEDERAL GOVERNMENT ON AN ANNUAL BASIS - FORM 990 WITH THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE. THIS RETURN IS SUBJECT TO EXAMINATION BY THIS AUTHORITY WITHIN CERTAIN STATUTORILY DEFINED PERIODS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 2
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: PETER ANTONELLIS IS THE FATHER OF DANIEL ANTONELLIS AND JOSEPH ANTONELLIS. THOMAS C. FRICANO AND DAVID FRICANO ARE BROTHERS. EDMUND GERBER IS THE FATHER OF ANDREW GERBER AND MICHELLE GERBER KASS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION HAS ITS FORM 990 PREPARED BY AN OUTSIDE ACCOUNTING FIRM AND HAS ESTABLISHED THE FOLLOWING REVIEW PROCESS TO ENSURE THAT THE INFORMATION REPORTED IS COMPLETE AND ACCURATE. WHEN THE FORM 990 HAS BEEN PREPARED, REVIEWED BY MANAGEMENT AND IS READY TO BE FILED WITH THE INTERNAL REVENUE SERVICE, IT IS PROVIDED TO THE MEMBERS OF THE ORGANIZATIONS GOVERNING BODY FOR ANY COMMENTS PRIOR TO ITS SUBMISSION. THE GOVERNING BODY IS PROVIDED WITH A REASONABLE AMOUNT OF TIME TO REVIEW THE FORM 990. ANY COMMENTS ARE THEN GROUPED, SUMMARIZED AND PROVIDED THROUGH MANAGEMENT TO THE OUTSIDE ACCOUNTING FIRM. ANY APPLICABLE ISSUES ARE ADDRESSED PRIOR TO THE RETURN BEING FINALIZED AND APPROVED FOR FILING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION CURRENTLY HAS IN PLACE A CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY WHICH IT REGULARLY MONITORS AND ENFORCES. THE BOARD MANDATES THAT ALL MEMBERS OF MANAGEMENT AND THE GOVERNING BODY SIGN A CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY ANNUALLY AND DISCLOSE ANY POTENTIAL OR ACTUAL CONFLICTS THAT MAY EXIST. IF A POTENTIAL OR ACTUAL CONFLICT OF INTEREST EXISTS, GOVERNING BODY AND MANAGEMENT WILL INVESTIGATE THE ISSUE. IF A CONFLICT OF INTEREST IS DETERMINED TO EXIST MANAGEMENT AND THE GOVERNING BODY WILL BE NOTIFIED IMMEDIATELY. THE MEMBER WILL NOT BE ALLOWED TO VOTE OR BE A PART OF ANY DECISIONS ABOUT ANY SUCH TRANSACTIONS THAT HAVE TO DO WITH THE CONFLICT UNTIL SUCH TIME THAT THERE IS NO LONGER A CONFLICT.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE COMPENSATION OF THE ORGANIZATION'S MANAGEMENT AND KEY EMPLOYEES IS REVIEWED AND APPROVED BY THE BOARD OF TRUSTEES, AN INDEPENDENT BODY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS FORM 990 AVAILABLE FOR PUBLIC INSPECTION AS REQUIRED UNDER SECTION 6104 OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE BY UPON WRITTEN REQUEST AT THE ORGANIZATIONS OFFICE AT 88 HUNTINGTON STREET NEW BRUNSWICK, NJ 08901. IN ADDITION FORM 1023 AS WELL AS THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS, AND CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY ARE AVAILABLE UPON WRITTEN REQUEST AT THE ORGANIZATIONS OFFICE.

THE ORGANIZATION IS REQUIRED TO FOLLOW THE AUDIT REQUIREMENTS OF TITLE 2 U.S. CODE OF FEDERAL REGULATIONS PART 200, UNIFORM ADMINISTRATIVE REQUIREMENTS, COST PRINCIPLES, AND AUDIT REQUIREMENTS FOR FEDERAL AWARDS(UNIFORM GUIDANCE) WHICH SUPERCEDES OMB CIRCULAR A-133.
